	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_EU_CAMEL_RIFLEMAN">
			<Text>[ICON_IDEOLOGY_AUTOCRACY] Camel Rifleman</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_EU_CAMEL_RIFLEMAN_HELP">
			<Text>Fast Industrial Era ranged Unit, excels at hit and run tactics. </Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_EU_CAMEL_RIFLEMAN_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Camel Rifleman is a powerful ranged attack unit, allowing it to do damage to enemies 2 hexes away. It may move after combat, receives +33% attack bonus when attacking from and +33% defense bonus while defending in Desert tiles, and adjacent enemy units receive -10% Combat Strength.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_EU_CAMEL_RIFLEMAN_PEDIA">
			<Text>
				The Camel Rifleman is an Industrial Era melee unit, available at the discovery of Gunpowder. It becomes obsolete at the discovery of Combustion, at which time it may upgrade to the Landship unit.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Some Muslim cavalrymen rode camels into battle. This often had an unsettling effect upon European-bred horses that had not before encountered those unusual beasts. As might be expected, camels are better-suited to desert terrain than are horses. Generally, the Camel Rifleman employed hit-and-run tactics against the enemy, more similar to Mongol horse archers than to knights or other heavy cavalry units. A well-trained Camel Rifleman unit could be extremely difficult for knights to deal with, if those knights were not protected by archers or their own light cavalry.
			</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>

